I live down the street from this Starbucks and I’m there about 2-3 times weekly. I sometimes sit and observe for a while also. I gave them a few months to get it together because I know they just opened. But it’s always the same. No one knows what’s happening, they don’t have assigned stations... so you’ll get your drink and then need to ask them where your hot food is. Then they will all look at each other and ask who’s doing what. 🙄 if it’s not busy, they are all standing around talking and laughing and then asking “what was your drink?” while people come in looking for it. And I think it’s a training store or something because they always have ALOT of people working there but some are just standing there watching other people doing things. if there is a manager on staff I never know who it is. They are either TOO relaxed and don’t care or never there. It’s really like a hangout for these guys working here and they just get paid. If it wasn’t for the new store and the drive though I wouldn’t come here. Also, unless your studying and not lounging the furniture that is supposed to be comfortable is not. They can be kinda rude too when THEY mess up your order and have to remake it. It kinda overall sucks here. Hopefully they will get new management to get it functioning properly.

I just came back from this place and I had to give a review before I forget. I ordered Mocha Crumble Frap but it came out to be just like a Java Chip Frap. I ordered this same drink before from another starbucks location and it looks and taste nothing like Java Chip Frap. When I went up to the barista to let him know, he just turned around and said "what." And instead of offering to replace my drink, he said he would put whipped cream in another cup. Like WHAT? What am I gonna do with that whipped cream? I would expect to see some basic manners from someone involved in the service business. Especially for a starbucks that just opened up.  I would drive 5 more mins down the road to the other starbucks where the baristas have excellent service and are friendly.
